1
00:01:29,860 --> 00:01:34,940
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,259 --> 00:01:37,940
[Episode 17]

3
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,050
It's installed?

4
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:41,710
You're here?

5
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:42,770
Thanks. Thank you.

6
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:44,870
Well. It's like this.

7
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:45,710
There's something

8
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:47,120
I have to tell you.

9
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:49,200
After you left that day,

10
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:50,150
I found out

11
00:01:50,350 --> 00:01:53,039
the landlord had rented this place out.

12
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:53,910
Rented out?

13
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:57,370
Didn't I give you the deposit?

14
00:01:57,430 --> 00:01:59,000
You have no respect for contracts.

15
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,200
Yeah. Don't worry.

16
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,850
I will definitely refund
the deposit to you.

17
00:02:01,850 --> 00:02:02,310
Refund?

18
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,130
We agreed when we signed the contract.

19
00:02:05,710 --> 00:02:07,790
If we back out, no refund.

20
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:09,400
If you back out,

21
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:10,470
you owe us double the deposit.

22
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:11,000
Double.

23
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:11,590
-Right?
-Wait. Wait.

24
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:12,590
Look, that day I...

25
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:13,310
Hurry up.

26
00:02:13,330 --> 00:02:14,120
The landlord is here.

27
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,280
You can have a talk.

28
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:15,630
What's wrong?

29
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:17,829
These are the 2 tenants I told you about.

30
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,120
Don't point at me.

31
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,000
Da?

32
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,590
You...

33
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:24,000
Didn't you go to Shenzhen?

34
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,560
Why are you back?

35
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,590
Do you know each other?

36
00:02:25,590 --> 00:02:26,360
Too well.

37
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:27,560
That's great.

38
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,360
Okay, okay. You can go.

39
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,079
We'll talk.

40
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:30,400
Okay. I'll get going then.

41
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,400
Contact me if you need anything.

42
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,190
Okay.

43
00:02:32,410 --> 00:02:32,870
I'm leaving.

44
00:02:32,870 --> 00:02:34,590
Wait, what about the dep... deposit?

45
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:35,960
I have the deposit.

46
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,240
Wait, what are you doing?

47
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,360
Are you renting a shop?

48
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,760
I came back from Beijing.

49
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:43,400
I got some top-notch goods
from the wholesale market.

50
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,710
I'm opening a shop with Xiaoman.

51
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:45,870
We were thinking
of taking over this place.

52
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:46,800
And we ended up taking over your shop.

53
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:47,430
What a coincidence.

54
00:02:47,430 --> 00:02:49,430
Nice. You're getting a shop going.

55
00:02:49,910 --> 00:02:50,680
Alright.

56
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,750
I'll give you your deposit back later.

57
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:52,590
Once you make a profit,

58
00:02:52,590 --> 00:02:53,400
you can pay me back.

59
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:53,840
Okay?

60
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:54,920
Is that okay?

61
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:55,310
Wait.

62
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:56,840
Why didn't you tell us you were back?

63
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,630
I wanted to surprise you.

64
00:02:58,630 --> 00:03:00,560
I didn't expect to run into you today.

65
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,120
What?

66
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,080
Follow me. I'll take you somewhere.

67
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:03,870
A surprise right now?

68
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:04,840
Hurry.

69
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:05,960
Come on.

70
00:03:07,150 --> 00:03:08,520
I've got to show you something today

71
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,250
that you've never seen before.

72
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,940
Do you remember where this is?

73
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,180
Isn't this the small stadium?

74
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:19,350
That's quite an idea.

75
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,560
You built a dance hall from scratch.

76
00:03:24,430 --> 00:03:26,290
It's like the Sydney Opera House.

77
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,280
Does it feel like our Workers' Dance Hall?

78
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:32,110
I was too young
for the Workers' Dance Hall.

79
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:33,790
I only went a couple of times.

80
00:03:35,910 --> 00:03:36,540
Da.

81
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:38,990
Look at this place.

82
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,510
Have you stayed in the south for too long?

83
00:03:42,510 --> 00:03:43,840
This is the Northeast.

84
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:45,710
You built an open-air dance hall,

85
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:47,310
but how many warm days do we get a year?

86
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:48,800
What will you do when it's cold?

87
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,079
You don't get it.

88
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:50,910
See this?

89
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,400
What is this for?

90
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,400
Skating.

91
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:56,560
It's great to skate here in winter.

92
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:58,000
We can dance inside, right?

93
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,120
Just shake it.

94
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,080
Good idea.

95
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:03,760
Come and help me out.

96
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,400
Me?

97
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,550
I'm opening a dance hall.

98
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,410
I invested all the money I had

99
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:12,430
with Sen in the clothing business.

100
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:14,190
I don't need you to pay anything.

101
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:15,920
I'll give you shares directly.

102
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,360
It won't be much, though.

103
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,920
But you'll still be a boss.

104
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:20,450
You won't be working for me.

105
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,400
Then what would I do here?

106
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:25,790
I won't beat around the bush.

107
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:26,810
It's like this.

108
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,390
Since I came back this time,

109
00:04:29,830 --> 00:04:31,630
I've found that Zhigang now has

110
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:33,120
a lot of his own ideas.

111
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:35,060
I'm not saying his ideas are wrong.

112
00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:36,270
But our ways of thinking

113
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:38,200
are just too different sometimes.

114
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,560
So right now,

115
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:42,600
I need a buffer between us.

116
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,240
Isn't Dongdong at home?

117
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,700
And isn't Nana there, too?

118
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:48,750
Dongdong is my brother,

119
00:04:48,750 --> 00:04:49,830
and Nana is my wife.

120
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:51,000
So whatever they say,

121
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,270
isn't it essentially me saying it?

122
00:04:52,270 --> 00:04:53,270
You're different.

123
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:54,480
Zhigang knows well

124
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,020
that you're not someone
who can be easily pushed around.

125
00:04:57,020 --> 00:04:58,020
Once you're here,

126
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,240
you can create a balance between us.

127
00:05:02,380 --> 00:05:03,770
It's okay, no rush.

128
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:05,930
I know what your concerns are.

129
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:10,040
Well, we just started getting
the hang of this clothing business.

130
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:13,070
Besides, I can't just abandon him.

131
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:17,510
You two can come
and work together, how about that?

132
00:05:17,510 --> 00:05:18,120
Bro.

133
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:20,800
Poaching my partner right in front of me,

134
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,830
isn't that a bit inappropriate?

135
00:05:21,830 --> 00:05:22,720
Well. You can't even manage

136
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,720
that little shop of yours yourself?

137
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:27,630
Our clothing business is getting better.

138
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:28,870
Wouldn't coming to work with you

139
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:30,310
be a bit of a waste of our talent?

140
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:32,470
You can't even afford the rent.
Getting better?

141
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:33,240
In what way?

142
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,070
Wang Tieda, you've gone too far.

143
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,830
I know you're eager for talent.

144
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:38,360
Okay, okay. Just save it for a second.

145
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,159
Listen to me.

146
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,890
While I was in the south,

147
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,140
I saw something called a mobile shop.

148
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:46,640
You two buy a caravan to sell clothes

149
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,260
and park it right outside our dance hall.

150
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:52,270
You're struggling with rent right now.

151
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,470
With that money,

152
00:05:53,470 --> 00:05:55,670
you could stock up on some decent goods.

153
00:05:58,310 --> 00:06:00,040
I'd say you've got brains.

154
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:01,430
Alright.

155
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,270
This is a powerful alliance.

156
00:06:04,270 --> 00:06:06,440
Don't worry. I will

157
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:09,730
bring some popularity
to your entertainment business.

158
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,160
I... I can dance and sing.

159
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:12,930
Right?

160
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:13,830
Thank you.

161
00:06:15,430 --> 00:06:16,160
Absolutely.

162
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:18,900
Look at your partner.
He's so interested.

163
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,160
Da,

164
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,670
why did you come back
to open a dance hall?

165
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:26,650
Why else? To make money.

166
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:30,240
I saved up some money
I earned in the south.

167
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,480
I always wanted to

168
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:34,159
come back and start a business for us.

169
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,310
Nothing else?

170
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:40,800
To be honest,

171
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,260
coming back this time,

172
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:47,840
I found that things are changing too fast.

173
00:06:48,070 --> 00:06:49,730
What used to be on these walls?

174
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:53,120
Now it says
"Reform and Tackling Key Challenges",

175
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,490
and "Downsizing for Efficiency".

176
00:06:57,870 --> 00:06:59,430
Da, so what I mean is

177
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:03,890
we can do anything,

178
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,140
as long as you want to do it.

179
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:09,170
With the money you earned in the south,

180
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,220
think it over carefully.

181
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:20,780
Anyway, I can't change the big picture.

182
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:24,020
It's just that when I get up at night,

183
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:26,740
I don't want to see
our factory pitch black.

184
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:31,630
Da.

185
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:33,240
Flip the switch.

186
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,310
Get ready.

187
00:07:34,830 --> 00:07:37,360
One, two, three!

188
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:40,510
[East Chemical Plant Workers' Dance Hall]

189
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,120
It works!

190
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:44,320
East Chemical Plant Workers' Dance Hall
is officially open!

191
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:45,170
Great!

192
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,240
Hello?

193
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:14,040
Xiaodan?

194
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,020
It's me.

195
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:16,350
I know it's you.

196
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,000
Let me tell you,

197
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,160
our Workers' Dance Hall

198
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:22,160
officially opened today.

199
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,630
It's so beautiful.

200
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:25,060
The lighting is amazing.

201
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,190
If only you were here.

202
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:27,430
You'd definitely love it.

203
00:08:27,430 --> 00:08:29,680
From what you say, it must be beautiful.

204
00:08:31,070 --> 00:08:32,549
I wish I were there.

205
00:08:32,549 --> 00:08:33,610
I want to see it too.

206
00:08:33,870 --> 00:08:35,750
Let me tell you,

207
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,960
when you come back for summer break,

208
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,130
we'll have a place to hang out here.

209
00:08:39,130 --> 00:08:41,190
We can roller skate in the afternoon,

210
00:08:41,539 --> 00:08:42,960
and hit the dance hall at night.

211
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,360
When the music starts,

212
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,910
I'll set up my barbecue stand,

213
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:46,630
chill some beer,

214
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:47,550
and get some watermelon.

215
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:48,680
It'll be so much fun.

216
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,100
This place will be your
summer getaway from now on.

217
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:51,740
You know?

218
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:54,440
Hey,

219
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:57,710
have you decided when
you're coming back for the holiday?

220
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:02,600
I might not make it back this holiday.

221
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:04,600
Why not?

222
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:06,910
I signed up for a language class.

223
00:09:07,730 --> 00:09:09,190
There are a lot of lessons.

224
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:10,910
Studying.

225
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,480
Well,

226
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:14,520
that's fine.

227
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,480
When I'm done with this busy period,

228
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,950
I'll find time to come visit you.

229
00:09:17,950 --> 00:09:18,680
No need.

230
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,720
You just got things settled
after the factory explosion.

231
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,720
Don't get distracted because of me.

232
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:25,210
Just focus on your work.

233
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,870
Right. I didn't handle that well.

234
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:34,120
But the dance hall business

235
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,520
is really different now.

236
00:09:35,870 --> 00:09:37,530
You'll see when you come back.

237
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,200
Bye.

238
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:55,810
You're here.

239
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:56,870
Xia,

240
00:09:58,510 --> 00:10:00,320
is this your first internship?

241
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:01,910
Yes, Mr. Li.

242
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,720
You don't need to be so nervous.

243
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:06,150
Although Director Yan
put in a good word for you,

244
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:07,670
we offered you this internship

245
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:08,870
because we were impressed

246
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:09,790
by your performance at school

247
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:11,550
and your academic background.

248
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:15,480
The company has hired
many new interns in the last 2 years,

249
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:17,150
and they've all been excellent.

250
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:19,200
You need to get up to speed quickly too.

251
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,200
I'll do my best.

252
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:24,160
I didn't expect to meet you here.

253
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:26,270
I've only been here for half a month.

254
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:28,630
I'm still figuring out
the specifics of the job.

255
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,120
You've been here for half a month.

256
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,600
Why didn't you tell me?

257
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,500
I didn't know you were coming.

258
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:35,720
We haven't been in touch
for so many years.

259
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:36,960
How was I supposed to tell you?

260
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,750
If I had known you were here,

261
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,840
I could have asked for your advice.

262
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,200
There are so many companies in Shanghai.

263
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:42,600
Right?

264
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,440
You could have given me some pointers.

265
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:45,720
What job you look for

266
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,320
depends on what suits you.

267
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:48,910
Have some coffee.

268
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:51,270
I've never had it before.

269
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,080
What is this? It's so bitter.

270
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,270
You'll get used to it.

271
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:03,270
Your internship has just begun.

272
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:04,110
Good luck.

273
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,000
You're early.

274
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:15,800
Good morning.

275
00:11:23,710 --> 00:11:25,590
Hello, Aoxun Technology.

276
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:27,450
Aoxun Technology.

277
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:28,980
Hello, Aoxun Technology.

278
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,360
Ma'am. Aoxun Technology.

279
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,390
Young man.

280
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:39,750
-Do you want...
-Are you...

281
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,360
Are you an intern?

282
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:42,600
Yes.

283
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:45,890
You wear leather shoes
for ground promotion?

284
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:48,090
Are you out of your mind?

285
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:50,240
It's the company dress code.

286
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,510
Rules only pick on honest people.

287
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:55,890
Even if you wore cloth shoes,

288
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:58,840
would your boss come to
the street to catch you?

289
00:11:58,870 --> 00:11:59,870
What do you think?

290
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:00,550
Yeah.

291
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,480
Sit down for a bit.

292
00:12:02,850 --> 00:12:03,660
Thanks, sir.

293
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,720
Sir, take a look at this.

294
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,870
If you want to change agents,

295
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:16,930
you can contact me.

296
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,750
Oh, that's a lot.

297
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:22,360
Young man,

298
00:12:22,910 --> 00:12:23,910
come, sit closer.

299
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:26,790
Let me tell you something.

300
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:27,870
The shops here

301
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:30,480
all have channels
they've worked with for over 10 years.

302
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,320
They sent you here for ground promotion

303
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:34,580
without expecting you to succeed at all.

304
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,870
The shops that are likely to sign

305
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:39,040
were all given to the old timers.

306
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,960
Why would they give them
to an intern like you?

307
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:41,890
Don't you think?

308
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,360
But if I can make a deal,

309
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:45,870
it'll be my first one.

310
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,320
Listen to me, young man.

311
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:50,250
You really have been brainwashed.

312
00:12:51,150 --> 00:12:52,840
They just want to torment you

313
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,840
to see if you're obedient.

314
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:56,440
My advice is,

315
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,860
go buy a pair of cloth shoes
on the street,

316
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,670
walk around for a bit, and then go back.

317
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:01,840
They won't care.

318
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,740
Alright, leave this here.

319
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,960
I'll contact you if I need anything.

320
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:07,800
Okay, then.

321
00:13:07,830 --> 00:13:09,080
Call me if you need to.

322
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:10,150
Okay.

323
00:13:12,590 --> 00:13:14,590
Not many people for the opening day.

324
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:18,550
Don't worry, it's just the first day.

325
00:13:18,870 --> 00:13:20,720
The dance hall tonight is the main event.

326
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:21,320
Besides,

327
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,920
a lot of people
don't know about this place yet.

328
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:27,120
Skating?

329
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,320
Yes, I need a pair of skates.

330
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,610
Okay. Go over there to change.

331
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:30,670
Here's the ticket.

332
00:13:34,030 --> 00:13:35,390
What size?

333
00:13:35,870 --> 00:13:36,600
38.

334
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,270
38.

335
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:38,730
Here. These will do.

336
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:40,250
Have a seat. I'll bring it over.

337
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:40,850
Thank you.

338
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:43,030
Make sure it's tied tight.

339
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,240
Okay. Thanks.

340
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:49,700
Miss. Miss.

341
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,530
You're not from our plant, are you?

342
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,460
Zhang Xiaoman.

343
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,150
Chunchun, right?

344
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:05,840
Yes.

345
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:06,630
Is it really you?

346
00:14:06,630 --> 00:14:07,360
Aren't you from Tiecheng?

347
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,320
What are you doing here?

348
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:09,510
What? Only you can come here,

349
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:10,750
and I can't?

350
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,280
Of course you can. Welcome.

351
00:14:12,390 --> 00:14:13,360
My friends and I

352
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:15,270
set it up together.

353
00:14:15,570 --> 00:14:16,690
You set it up?

354
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,960
So you're the boss now.

355
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:18,510
Impressive.

356
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:19,750
What boss?

357
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:21,630
It's just a small business.

358
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,600
If you like to have fun,

359
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:25,720
we have roller skating in the afternoon,

360
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:29,030
and a dance hall, drinks,
and music at night.

361
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:29,870
Come often.

362
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,150
Okay. Tonight,

363
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:32,430
I'll change into something nice
and come dance.

364
00:14:32,430 --> 00:14:33,690
Come. I'll give you free drinks.

365
00:14:33,690 --> 00:14:34,690
Okay. I'm off.

366
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,320
Xiaoman!

367
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:38,790
Xiaoman!

368
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,030
Da.

369
00:14:40,210 --> 00:14:40,960
I need a few people

370
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,220
to unload the flowers.

371
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,030
Where did you get these?

372
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,090
Zhigang, hurry up.

373
00:14:44,970 --> 00:14:46,080
Want a soda?

374
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:47,390
What flavors do you have?

375
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:48,030
Orange.

376
00:14:48,230 --> 00:14:49,360
Sure, I'll take one.

377
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:51,480
What's your name?

378
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:52,650
Ye Chunchun.

379
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:53,670
Just call me Chunchun.

380
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:54,120
Okay,

381
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:54,740
Chunchun.

382
00:14:54,950 --> 00:14:55,460
Cheers.

383
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:17,000
These buses are way too hot.

384
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,510
You must be Mr. Cui.

385
00:15:18,870 --> 00:15:20,030
Welcome.

386
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:20,830
Welcome.

387
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,600
Nice to meet you, Mr. Cui.

388
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,750
Please, come on inside.

389
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,030
This way, please.

390
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:24,840
Welcome. Please come in.

391
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,360
Come on, buddy.

392
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,360
Everyone inside.

393
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:26,840
Please come in.

394
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,100
Sit wherever you like.

395
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:29,240
Welcome.

396
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:29,790
Who is he?

397
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,120
Who cares?

398
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:32,840
Take good care of all these people.

399
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:33,870
Keep in touch with them.

400
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:35,030
If one person has fun dancing,

401
00:15:35,030 --> 00:15:35,910
they'll bring a partner next time.

402
00:15:35,910 --> 00:15:36,790
Partners bring partners,

403
00:15:36,790 --> 00:15:37,960
and this place will blow up.

404
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,000
Understood.

405
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,800
Come on in. Please, inside.

406
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,840
Da, your connections

407
00:15:47,670 --> 00:15:48,630
are really something.

408
00:15:48,630 --> 00:15:50,030
They aren't really mine.

409
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:50,910
It's the first day of business,

410
00:15:50,910 --> 00:15:52,670
and you have a whole busload
of people here.

411
00:15:52,670 --> 00:15:54,750
Didn't you ask me
who that old guy was earlier?

412
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:55,270
Who is he?

413
00:15:55,270 --> 00:15:57,600
That's Tiecheng's Dance King
from twenty years ago.

414
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,390
For real?

415
00:15:58,410 --> 00:15:59,520
No joke.

416
00:15:59,670 --> 00:16:02,080
Whenever a new entertainment venue opens,
he's there.

417
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:02,920
And,

418
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:04,870
he has a whole crowd following him.

419
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,650
If you take good care of him,

420
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:08,440
and I'm telling you,
our place will be a hit.

421
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,240
Don't worry.

422
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,700
I'll definitely win over
a client like that.

423
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:14,020
Did he come all the way from Tiecheng?

424
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:15,880
He really loves to dance.

425
00:16:18,990 --> 00:16:20,150
Da, I'm going downstairs for a bit.

426
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:20,700
Go ahead.

427
00:16:25,550 --> 00:16:27,960
Okay.

428
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,750
Let me tell you.

429
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:31,030
Hardly anyone truly understands the waltz

430
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:31,720
these days.

431
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:34,060
Most people think
that just clutching each other

432
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:35,050
counts as a dance.

433
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:36,150
That's just nonsense.

434
00:16:36,150 --> 00:16:37,030
When dancing, the man

435
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:38,550
has to be like a pillar, you know,

436
00:16:38,550 --> 00:16:39,480
supporting the woman.

437
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,150
And then: pop, he makes her bloom

438
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:42,550
just like a firework.

439
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,840
You dance really well, though.

440
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:45,790
I'm just messing around.

441
00:16:45,790 --> 00:16:47,790
If you like it here, please come often.

442
00:16:47,790 --> 00:16:48,360
Okay.

443
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:48,870
Okay.

444
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:51,470
-You. You wanna chat?
-Yeah.

445
00:16:54,910 --> 00:16:55,750
You actually came.

446
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,120
Didn't you ask me to?

447
00:16:57,620 --> 00:16:58,750
You sure were quick.

448
00:16:59,270 --> 00:17:00,200
What do you want to drink? It's on me.

449
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,670
I'll have a cold beer.

450
00:17:01,670 --> 00:17:02,470
I'm roasting.

451
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:03,480
Don't you want something more expensive?

452
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:04,940
Do you two know each other?

453
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:07,400
We've known each other for years.

454
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,270
It's a good chance
for everyone to get acquainted.

455
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:10,400
We'll be working side by side

456
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,920
from here on out.

457
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:13,440
Mr. Cui.

458
00:17:14,030 --> 00:17:15,550
You've still got it.

459
00:17:15,550 --> 00:17:17,109
Those steps were so smooth.

460
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,400
Really, you know your stuff.

461
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,200
To be honest, this kind of elegance

462
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,460
has no market anymore.

463
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,680
It's only been a few years
since we last met.

464
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,310
When did you start doing this?

465
00:17:28,310 --> 00:17:29,440
What's wrong with you?

466
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:30,640
Aren't you just a lousy errand boy?

467
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,170
What are you so cocky about?

468
00:17:33,630 --> 00:17:35,290
Sweetie, have a dance with me.

469
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,640
Sure. Five yuan a dance.

470
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:39,130
I'll take one.

471
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:39,480
Deal.

472
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:41,680
Let's go.

473
00:18:09,380 --> 00:18:12,180
How do you feel after doing field marketing
for the last two weeks?

474
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:13,040
I'm exhausted.

475
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:15,960
I feel like
I've walked the entire district.

476
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:17,860
Right now,

477
00:18:17,890 --> 00:18:19,720
I just want to sit in this chair

478
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:23,350
and get comfortable.

479
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:31,200
But

480
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,310
I closed nine deals.

481
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:36,440
Among all interns
in this company's history,

482
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:37,770
that is the best record.

483
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:43,550
It seems you have the potential
to be a sales champion.

484
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:44,590
Right?

485
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:47,230
Keep up the good work.

486
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:55,900
Taking a break?

487
00:18:57,940 --> 00:18:58,620
Want a cola?

488
00:18:58,990 --> 00:18:59,710
No, thanks.

489
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,720
Well, um...

490
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:07,760
Yesterday...

491
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,510
I didn't mean anything by it.

492
00:19:09,510 --> 00:19:11,880
I just realized it's been years
since we last saw each other,

493
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:12,590
so...

494
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:14,510
I was just asking

495
00:19:14,510 --> 00:19:16,160
out of curiosity. Don't overthink it

496
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:17,490
or take it the wrong way.

497
00:19:18,150 --> 00:19:19,610
I really didn't mean that.

498
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,930
Let's have a drink. Come on.

499
00:19:32,830 --> 00:19:34,790
Where are those two friends of yours?

500
00:19:34,790 --> 00:19:35,640
Who do you mean?

501
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:36,770
Xia Lei and Xiaodan?

502
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:39,960
They're both in college now.

503
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:41,160
They're doing great.

504
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:43,290
That's impressive.

505
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,350
Then what are you so cocky about?

506
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:48,090
You stayed in your hometown

507
00:19:48,090 --> 00:19:49,930
and don't even have a real job now.

508
00:19:49,930 --> 00:19:50,920
What kind of talk is that?

509
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,450
Are you making fun of me now?

510
00:19:52,510 --> 00:19:54,310
What do you mean by "no real job"?

511
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:56,200
I'm a full-time employee here.

512
00:19:56,390 --> 00:19:57,740
I'm just

513
00:19:58,120 --> 00:20:00,640
temporarily on standby.

514
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:03,680
Fine.

515
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,030
Come on. To your honorable standby.

516
00:20:06,030 --> 00:20:06,890
Here's to that.

517
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,790
Really? Listen to you.

518
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:12,680
Well, you drink...

519
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:13,680
What does that mean?

520
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:14,940
You're on standby too?

521
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,830
After I finished high school,

522
00:20:17,830 --> 00:20:19,160
I found a few jobs.

523
00:20:19,710 --> 00:20:22,240
But I got fired before long.

524
00:20:22,830 --> 00:20:25,110
Later, I joined a proper work unit.

525
00:20:25,410 --> 00:20:27,970
But soon enough, I ran it into the ground.

526
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,750
You ran the place into the ground?

527
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,610
You... You're really something.

528
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:35,480
So you came here.

529
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:36,880
You're afraid of

530
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,720
bumping into people you know
in Tiecheng, right?

531
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:40,380
Why the hell would I be afraid?

532
00:20:40,470 --> 00:20:42,070
Where I dance,

533
00:20:42,110 --> 00:20:43,920
husbands ride their bikes

534
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,250
to drop their wives off.

535
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:47,970
But didn't the Hammer Gang
show up in Tiecheng?

536
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:51,010
The Hammer Gang is in Tiecheng？

537
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,200
And those bastards

538
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,500
target dancing ladies.

539
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:56,730
I heard they've killed two already.

540
00:20:56,730 --> 00:20:57,730
Oh my god.

541
00:20:58,750 --> 00:21:00,010
Then don't stay there.

542
00:21:00,580 --> 00:21:01,440
It's too scary.

543
00:21:02,750 --> 00:21:04,640
Just hang out here with us from now on.

544
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:05,960
It's safe here, right?

545
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,840
Everyone's familiar.
We know each other well.

546
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:10,740
And the place is clean.

547
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:13,350
If you have any good friends

548
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:14,200
over there,

549
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,030
bring them all here.

550
00:21:15,030 --> 00:21:16,370
Still drumming up business?

551
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:17,520
Isn't it lively?

552
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:21,350
Alright, I've got a customer.

553
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:22,610
Return my shoes for me.

554
00:21:26,830 --> 00:21:28,060
870,

555
00:21:28,770 --> 00:21:29,830
plus ticket sales,

556
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:31,980
makes it only 900 yuan.

557
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,510
Isn't 800 or 900 a day pretty good?

558
00:21:35,510 --> 00:21:37,310
That's 20,000 or 30,000 a month.

559
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,200
Da,

560
00:21:38,830 --> 00:21:40,550
this is just revenue.

561
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,160
You haven't counted
the contracting fee yet.

562
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,310
It is the main cost.

563
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:46,070
Plus tickets and those wages—

564
00:21:46,710 --> 00:21:47,910
how much will be left?

565
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,110
Why the rush?

566
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,490
It's only our first day.

567
00:21:51,490 --> 00:21:53,020
Word hasn't gotten out yet.

568
00:21:53,110 --> 00:21:54,240
Once everyone knows,

569
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:55,900
people will come flooding in.

570
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,070
I hope so.

571
00:22:28,260 --> 00:22:29,640
Hey, Miss. Looking for clothes?

572
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:30,270
Check out my goods.

573
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:32,070
-Let us have a look.
-Have a look.

574
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:33,240
Look at this one.

575
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,350
You have great taste.

576
00:22:34,350 --> 00:22:35,160
You picked this one right away.

577
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:35,720
Yeah.

578
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,110
If you wear my clothes,

579
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:37,920
I guarantee

580
00:22:38,110 --> 00:22:40,930
you'll have everyone turning
to look at you on the street.

581
00:22:40,930 --> 00:22:41,520
You two.

582
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:42,030
Chunchun.

583
00:22:42,030 --> 00:22:43,490
You're open for business?

584
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:45,440
Hey, Miss.

585
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:46,550
Your clothes are beautiful.

586
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:47,810
Where did you buy them?

587
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,180
I asked these two

588
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,800
to get it from Beijing for me.

589
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,920
The one you picked is also very nice.

590
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,790
I think you'll look great in it.

591
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:56,830
You have a better figure than me.

592
00:22:56,830 --> 00:22:57,680
It'll definitely look stylish.

593
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:58,310
Here, try it.

594
00:22:58,310 --> 00:22:59,510
How are these the same?

595
00:22:59,510 --> 00:23:01,000
How are they different, miss?

596
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,680
Same brand, different style.

597
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:03,960
Different style?
They're totally different.

598
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:04,920
They both have sequins.

599
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:05,350
Right.

600
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,480
How much is this one then?

601
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:08,210
Two hundred.

602
00:23:08,350 --> 00:23:08,960
Two hundred?

603
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,420
This is worth two hundred?

604
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:11,680
Tell you what, miss.

605
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:13,750
Since you share the same taste

606
00:23:13,750 --> 00:23:15,150
as my regular customers,

607
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:16,930
I'll give it to you two for 180.

608
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:17,680
Eighty.

609
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:18,480
Eighty.

610
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:19,640
Eighty?

611
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:20,480
Sold!

612
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:21,000
Sold.

613
00:23:21,090 --> 00:23:21,830
I'll bag it up for you.

614
00:23:21,830 --> 00:23:23,070
What are you doing, Xiaoman?

615
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:24,600
-Can you sell it at 80?
-Yes.

616
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:26,070
Is that even covering our costs, Xiaoman?

617
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:26,680
Alright.

618
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:27,610
Eighty. Come on.

619
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,680
Eighty doesn't even cover the cost, miss.

620
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:31,000
-No, you know?
-Eighty. Eighty. Eighty.

621
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,270
We sincerely want to buy it,

622
00:23:32,270 --> 00:23:33,660
and you want to sell it, right?

623
00:23:33,660 --> 00:23:35,920
Look how straightforward
this young man is.

624
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:36,790
Okay, okay. Eighty.

625
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:37,920
Okay. Pack it up.

626
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:38,480
Come back soon.

627
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:39,270
Take care.

628
00:23:39,870 --> 00:23:41,200
She can really bargain.

629
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:43,350
Getting 80 is good enough.

630
00:23:43,350 --> 00:23:45,200
I can't even stand
looking at it hanging there.

631
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,000
Stop talking.

632
00:23:46,470 --> 00:23:47,590
Do you even know the wholesale price?

633
00:23:47,590 --> 00:23:48,160
How much?

634
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:49,270
Thirty.

635
00:23:49,290 --> 00:23:50,730
-30 yuan?
-Yeah, 30.

636
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:54,110
Chunchun.

637
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,660
You are our lucky star.

638
00:23:57,030 --> 00:23:58,350
We've been stuck here all day,

639
00:23:58,350 --> 00:23:59,350
and haven't made a single sale.

640
00:23:59,350 --> 00:24:01,680
But as soon as you show up,
things start selling.

641
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,740
How about you
be our model from now on?

642
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:07,550
Just wear our clothes
and go dance in there.

643
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:08,680
When people like them and ask,

644
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:09,620
just tell them
you bought them at the entrance.

645
00:24:09,620 --> 00:24:10,680
We'll have the stock ready.

646
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:11,680
What do you think?

647
00:24:11,970 --> 00:24:13,690
It's a great idea.

648
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,780
What kind of idea is that?

649
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:16,650
You two are treating me like
a lucky cat mascot.

650
00:24:16,650 --> 00:24:19,000
No, look, we're partners, aren't we?

651
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:20,350
-Let's cooperate.
-Chunchun.

652
00:24:20,350 --> 00:24:21,870
Who said you're a lucky cat?

653
00:24:21,870 --> 00:24:23,230
You're a walking model.

654
00:24:23,750 --> 00:24:25,200
A living, breathing model.

655
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:26,440
And you are not just any model,

656
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:30,160
but the chief supermodel of JM!

657
00:24:30,470 --> 00:24:31,160
You know?

658
00:24:32,430 --> 00:24:33,690
There's a commission.

659
00:24:34,270 --> 00:24:35,530
It's worth your while.

660
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:36,450
Right?

661
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:37,540
Alright, alright.

662
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:44,480
Look at that.

663
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,240
Her outfit is so pretty!

664
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:48,960
Sis, where did you get that outfit?

665
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,200
This outfit...

666
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:51,070
It's really nice.

667
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:51,680
Really?

668
00:24:51,910 --> 00:24:53,130
I'm telling you, it's just at the entrance.

669
00:24:53,130 --> 00:24:55,790
There's a little cart by the gate,
I got it there.

670
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,000
-You can put it on and come back.
-Are they all your friends?

671
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:57,400
Yeah.

672
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:58,060
Take a look.

673
00:24:58,090 --> 00:24:59,030
-Have a look.
-Choose whatever you like.

674
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:00,160
-All of them.
-Oh my!

675
00:25:27,510 --> 00:25:28,940
There are only a few pieces left.

676
00:25:28,940 --> 00:25:31,580
I need to go to the wholesale market
to stock up on some trendy stuff.

677
00:25:31,580 --> 00:25:32,210
Okay.

678
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,200
Let's keep doing it this way.

679
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,400
Our business will be booming in no time.

680
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:37,850
What are you looking at?

681
00:25:41,670 --> 00:25:43,790
Oh my. They're stealing our electricity.

682
00:25:43,790 --> 00:25:44,590
Obviously.

683
00:25:46,950 --> 00:25:49,070
I knew a string of lights
was missing from the room.

684
00:25:49,070 --> 00:25:51,730
They even stripped the tinsel off the railings.

685
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,720
Keep a close watch on your brother.

686
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,240
His eyes are like a sieve all the time.

687
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,070
Forget it.

688
00:25:57,510 --> 00:25:58,270
Where are you going?

689
00:25:58,270 --> 00:25:59,880
I'm going to help Xiaoman.

690
00:25:59,880 --> 00:26:01,140
Look at you, all eager.

691
00:26:01,290 --> 00:26:01,800
Xiaoman.

692
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:03,730
Running off all eager like a puppy.

693
00:26:04,090 --> 00:26:05,200
These are selling fast.

694
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,100
[Aoxun Technology]

695
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,720
Are your Q3 marketing reports

696
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:09,520
finished yet?

697
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,070
Why not just ask those two interns

698
00:26:13,070 --> 00:26:14,440
to do it for you?

699
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:16,110
I'm not their mentor.

700
00:26:16,110 --> 00:26:17,590
What does that matter?

701
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:19,510
They're interns anyway.

702
00:26:19,530 --> 00:26:20,590
Giving them work

703
00:26:20,590 --> 00:26:22,890
is actually helping them improve themselves.

704
00:26:22,890 --> 00:26:24,420
Then which one should I ask?

705
00:26:24,490 --> 00:26:25,490
Ask the girl.

706
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:27,350
She looks like an easier target.

707
00:26:32,810 --> 00:26:34,400
Honey, what are you working on?

708
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:36,200
I'm doing the market info brief.

709
00:26:37,380 --> 00:26:38,050
Perfect.

710
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:39,320
I have a batch of

711
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:41,350
statistics of Marketing Department.

712
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:43,030
How about you help me count it?

713
00:26:43,250 --> 00:26:45,650
It'll be really helpful for your brief too.

714
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:46,640
Sorry.

715
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,480
Manager Li told me to send him the brief

716
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:49,480
before I get off work.

717
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:51,400
Well, once you're done with that,

718
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:54,260
you can just do
my statistical reports then, right?

719
00:26:54,990 --> 00:26:57,190
But if I've already finished the brief,

720
00:26:57,270 --> 00:27:00,070
how will the statistical reports
be helpful to me?

721
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:03,440
Sweetie, you're here for an internship.

722
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:04,400
Don't you want to learn?

723
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:06,800
This is such a great learning opportunity!

724
00:27:08,510 --> 00:27:10,750
Sorry, I'm a bit too clumsy.

725
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:12,820
Desk work isn't in my career plan.

726
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:29,100
Hey, handsome.

727
00:27:29,310 --> 00:27:29,960
Ms. Zhao.

728
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:32,080
I still have some tidying up to do.

729
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,950
You're quite diligent, aren't you?

730
00:27:33,950 --> 00:27:34,550
Come here.

731
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:36,100
Come here, come here.

732
00:27:36,590 --> 00:27:37,310
Sit down.

733
00:27:39,310 --> 00:27:40,110
What's up?

734
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,270
So, I've got a little something.

735
00:27:42,790 --> 00:27:44,050
Could you do me a favor?

736
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,030
What is it?

737
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:46,920
The marketing statistical reports.

738
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:48,580
Could you compile them for me?

739
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:49,640
Tonight,

740
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:50,880
I have a very important date.

741
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:51,940
I really have to go.

742
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:54,410
Could you work overtime for me, okay?

743
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:57,200
I'm still working on
our department's monthly report.

744
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,270
It's due today.

745
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:00,110
That's fine, I'm not in a rush.

746
00:28:00,110 --> 00:28:02,110
Just give it to me tomorrow morning.

747
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:09,160
Let me tell you,

748
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:11,270
back when I was an intern,

749
00:28:11,270 --> 00:28:13,880
I was buying coffee
and printing files for everyone.

750
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:15,000
I even had to work across departments

751
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,070
to learn different aspects of the job.

752
00:28:17,070 --> 00:28:18,030
Not every intern

753
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:19,760
gets an opportunity like this.

754
00:28:20,620 --> 00:28:23,050
I do want to learn more.

755
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:24,550
I'm telling you.

756
00:28:24,550 --> 00:28:25,350
Don't worry.

757
00:28:25,550 --> 00:28:26,310
When it comes time

758
00:28:26,310 --> 00:28:28,110
for the internship evaluation,

759
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:30,000
I'll ask Han

760
00:28:30,220 --> 00:28:32,220
to put in a few good words with Mr. Li.

761
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:33,590
Thank you, Ms. Zhao.

762
00:28:34,030 --> 00:28:35,830
No big deal. I'm rooting for you.

763
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:43,880
Why are you thanking her?

764
00:28:44,790 --> 00:28:46,990
I'm thanking her for think highly of me.

765
00:29:01,550 --> 00:29:02,400
Lei.

766
00:29:03,010 --> 00:29:03,620
Ms. Zhao.

767
00:29:04,110 --> 00:29:05,770
I'm counting on you this time.

768
00:29:05,980 --> 00:29:07,950
But you must give it to me tomorrow morning.

769
00:29:07,950 --> 00:29:09,870
Or Han will scold me again.

770
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:11,670
Sure. I'll get it done.

771
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:12,920
Thank you.

772
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:14,850
I'll bring you coffee tomorrow.

773
00:29:14,850 --> 00:29:15,410
Thanks.

774
00:29:16,220 --> 00:29:16,750
Bye-bye.

775
00:29:16,890 --> 00:29:17,530
Bye-bye.

776
00:29:17,700 --> 00:29:18,420
Let's go.

777
00:29:24,510 --> 00:29:25,480
You're done too?

778
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:27,750
You're not?

779
00:29:29,160 --> 00:29:30,030
My own work is done,

780
00:29:30,030 --> 00:29:32,290
but I have to help Marketing
with their reports.

781
00:29:32,290 --> 00:29:34,350
I guess I'll finish them around 10 PM.

782
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:35,830
If you do this,

783
00:29:36,270 --> 00:29:38,510
those in the loop will know
you're helping out,

784
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:39,920
But those who aren't might think
you're incompetent

785
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:40,920
and inefficient.

786
00:29:42,370 --> 00:29:43,280
No way.

787
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:45,480
It doesn't hurt to do a bit more.

788
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:21,200
Da.

789
00:30:25,270 --> 00:30:26,070
Da.

790
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:28,380
Looking sharp, young man.

791
00:30:29,730 --> 00:30:31,200
What are you doing up there?

792
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:32,200
Fixing the wires.

793
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:36,830
I brought your treasure back to you.

794
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:38,380
Safe and sound.

795
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:39,350
I polished it every day,

796
00:30:39,350 --> 00:30:41,180
changed the oil and brake fluid too.

797
00:30:41,180 --> 00:30:42,640
And I even filled the tank.

798
00:30:43,110 --> 00:30:43,770
Here you go.

799
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,480
What do you mean?

800
00:30:45,590 --> 00:30:46,740
I gave it to you, so it's yours now.

801
00:30:46,740 --> 00:30:48,160
How can you just give it to me?

802
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:49,790
You put so much effort into this bike.

803
00:30:49,790 --> 00:30:50,640
How could I accept it?

804
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,550
I can't ride this thing anymore.

805
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:54,920
Between drinking with bosses and clients,

806
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:56,450
I really have no time for it.

807
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,550
It's good for you now.

808
00:30:58,550 --> 00:31:00,080
It's useful for commuting.

809
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:03,280
So I got a free bike.

810
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:05,110
Bro,

811
00:31:05,510 --> 00:31:06,950
I'll keep it parked at my place then.

812
00:31:06,950 --> 00:31:09,350
I'll still clean and maintain it every day.

813
00:31:09,550 --> 00:31:11,150
But the bike is always yours.

814
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:13,110
Just say the word whenever you want to ride,

815
00:31:13,110 --> 00:31:14,710
and I'll bring it right over.

816
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:16,680
Give me a ride.

817
00:31:16,830 --> 00:31:18,070
Let's see how your riding skills are.

818
00:31:18,070 --> 00:31:18,920
No problem.

819
00:31:19,070 --> 00:31:19,600
Hurry up.

820
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:24,070
Oh my.

821
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:24,960
Slow down.

822
00:31:24,990 --> 00:31:25,740
It's fine.

823
00:31:25,910 --> 00:31:27,460
Come on. Helmet on.

824
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:30,980
I've never sat on the back seat in my life.

825
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,740
I haven't given rides to guys either.

826
00:31:56,110 --> 00:31:57,550
Where did you get this coffee?

827
00:31:57,550 --> 00:31:59,030
The new coffee shop downstairs.

828
00:31:59,030 --> 00:32:00,460
It should be pretty good, right?

829
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:01,990
Why didn't you bring me one?

830
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,590
That new coach...

831
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,720
is drop-dead gorgeous.

832
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:07,680
I know, right?

833
00:32:07,810 --> 00:32:09,240
Did you see his muscles?

834
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,070
Why don't you get his number for me?

835
00:32:14,070 --> 00:32:15,550
I have a feeling he's single.

836
00:32:15,550 --> 00:32:16,590
I'm not going to do that!

837
00:32:16,590 --> 00:32:17,680
Why?

838
00:32:18,830 --> 00:32:19,920
I'm... I'm too shy.

839
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:21,250
Go get it for me, please.

840
00:32:21,510 --> 00:32:22,550
But seriously,

841
00:32:22,570 --> 00:32:25,140
that coach is handsome and tall.

842
00:32:25,590 --> 00:32:26,510
Don't get any ideas.

843
00:32:26,510 --> 00:32:27,440
I saw him first.

844
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:29,300
I won't fight you for him.

845
00:32:30,550 --> 00:32:32,880
How about this?
I'll get his number for you,

846
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:35,010
and you treat me to the new restaurant.

847
00:32:36,310 --> 00:32:37,030
I'll think about it.

848
00:32:37,030 --> 00:32:38,830
If you can get it…

849
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:40,590
Ms. Zhao.

850
00:32:40,590 --> 00:32:42,350
I've finished the Q3 market report.

851
00:32:42,350 --> 00:32:43,030
Just leave it here.

852
00:32:43,030 --> 00:32:44,360
And I've emailed it to you, too.

853
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:45,290
Jiajia, listen.

854
00:32:45,370 --> 00:32:46,570
If you get the number,

855
00:32:47,310 --> 00:32:47,940
I'll treat you…

856
00:32:47,940 --> 00:32:48,750
The coffee...

857
00:32:48,750 --> 00:32:49,590
Thanks.

858
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,030
If you get it,

859
00:32:51,510 --> 00:32:52,880
I'll treat you
to the most expensive place.

860
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:53,680
Order whatever you want.

861
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:54,550
No problem!

862
00:32:54,590 --> 00:32:55,510
You promised.

863
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:57,710
You should just get a membership there.

864
00:33:08,570 --> 00:33:10,340
[Americano]

865
00:33:28,790 --> 00:33:30,110
Qiang, don't worry.

866
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:31,070
There's plenty.

867
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:35,350
Look at their place.

868
00:33:42,370 --> 00:33:43,040
Sir,

869
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:44,260
you here for skating?

870
00:33:44,260 --> 00:33:45,590
No. Where is Wang Tieda?

871
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:46,960
Looking for Da?

872
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:48,200
Yes. Da.

873
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,250
Well, a second, please.

874
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:51,160
Da!

875
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:52,880
Someone is looking for you.

876
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:53,830
Let him up.

877
00:33:54,510 --> 00:33:55,350
This way.

878
00:33:55,630 --> 00:33:56,410
Go in on the second floor.

879
00:33:56,410 --> 00:33:57,070
Go up to the second floor from here.

880
00:33:57,070 --> 00:33:57,550
Okay.

881
00:34:04,270 --> 00:34:04,880
Da.

882
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:06,240
Wei Si.

883
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:06,830
Wei Si.

884
00:34:07,110 --> 00:34:08,510
I've heard a lot about you, Da.

885
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:10,239
I'm so familiar with your name.

886
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:12,320
In Guangzhou, Blind Lu

887
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:13,850
always mentioned you to me.

888
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:18,230
This small place of ours is nice.

889
00:34:18,230 --> 00:34:20,070
You can attract so many young people here.

890
00:34:20,070 --> 00:34:22,270
And they can hang out here day and night.

891
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:23,350
Interesting.

892
00:34:24,230 --> 00:34:25,760
It's just a small business.

893
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:27,760
I'm just trying to make my ends meet.

894
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,159
You're being modest, Da.

895
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:32,000
I came here today

896
00:34:32,110 --> 00:34:32,969
for two things.

897
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:37,360
First, to congratulate you
on the opening of the dance hall.

898
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:37,989
Thank you.

899
00:34:38,010 --> 00:34:40,420
Second, I want to see if I can

900
00:34:40,659 --> 00:34:43,179
do some business with you, Da.

901
00:34:45,670 --> 00:34:46,400
Zhigang.

902
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:47,480
Zhigang.

903
00:34:48,639 --> 00:34:50,239
Bring up two bottles of soda.

904
00:34:52,860 --> 00:34:54,050
To be honest, Da,

905
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:55,070
I wanted to take over this place

906
00:34:55,070 --> 00:34:57,230
before you did.

907
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:58,590
But you beat me to it.

908
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:00,230
I don't mean anything by it.

909
00:35:00,230 --> 00:35:00,860
I'm just envious.

910
00:35:00,860 --> 00:35:02,370
I thought you looked familiar just now.

911
00:35:02,370 --> 00:35:03,430
Isn't this Boss Si?

912
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:05,480
Wait, this is...

913
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:06,230
Zhigang.

914
00:35:06,330 --> 00:35:07,710
I've heard so much about you.

915
00:35:07,710 --> 00:35:08,440
Truly.

916
00:35:10,980 --> 00:35:13,380
Didn't you mention some business just now?

917
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:15,510
Let me ask you,

918
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:18,510
how much do your ice rink and dance hall

919
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,030
make daily?

920
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:22,170
Are you comfortable to reveal?

921
00:35:25,150 --> 00:35:26,610
Two... over two thousand.

922
00:35:28,260 --> 00:35:29,490
That's too little!

923
00:35:30,600 --> 00:35:32,890
I used to manage venues in the South.

924
00:35:33,270 --> 00:35:34,670
I... I've summed it up.

925
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:38,510
Let's put aside
those fancy, high-end clubs

926
00:35:38,540 --> 00:35:40,070
and just talk about the average ones.

927
00:35:40,070 --> 00:35:42,670
If you just rely on tickets sales,

928
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:44,700
taking a cut from the girls' dances,

929
00:35:44,700 --> 00:35:45,590
and selling drinks,

930
00:35:45,590 --> 00:35:46,990
you won't make a fortune.

931
00:35:47,190 --> 00:35:48,790
If you want to make big money,

932
00:35:48,900 --> 00:35:51,130
you... you need to find another way.

933
00:35:51,790 --> 00:35:54,790
Boss Si, did you come here
with the idea of another way?

934
00:35:55,870 --> 00:35:56,420
Yes.

935
00:35:57,730 --> 00:35:58,690
What is it?

936
00:36:04,550 --> 00:36:05,610
The "cough syrup".

937
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:13,440
Boss Si.

938
00:36:14,070 --> 00:36:15,630
I run a legitimate dance hall here.

939
00:36:15,630 --> 00:36:16,760
I don't touch drugs.

940
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:18,670
It's fine to say that behind closed doors.

941
00:36:18,670 --> 00:36:20,630
Don't say it outside,
making people laugh at you.

942
00:36:20,630 --> 00:36:21,690
The "cough syrup",

943
00:36:21,710 --> 00:36:22,830
what... what is that?

944
00:36:22,830 --> 00:36:23,670
It's not drug.

945
00:36:23,670 --> 00:36:25,130
Isn't it just cough syrup?

946
00:36:25,710 --> 00:36:27,110
Right? With our climate,

947
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,800
wouldn't all the old folks

948
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:30,920
drink a few bottles in the winter?

949
00:36:30,980 --> 00:36:33,390
I did this business
when I was in the South.

950
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:34,280
You know?

951
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:35,320
The Phoenix, the Great World,

952
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,440
I supplied them all.

953
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:38,170
I-It's... absolutely s-safe.

954
00:36:39,830 --> 00:36:41,400
Right. But can this stuff

955
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:42,480
be sold at the bar?

956
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:43,550
If it can be sold at the bar,

957
00:36:43,550 --> 00:36:45,480
I'll order some from you right now.

958
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:48,440
Da, you're just being difficult.

959
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:50,060
No matter what,

960
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:50,760
well,

961
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:53,000
you can't sell it openly at the bar.

962
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:55,060
It is a prescription drug, after all.

963
00:36:55,070 --> 00:36:56,480
Right? Besides,

964
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:58,920
if you put it right on the bar,

965
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:00,110
where's the mystery?

966
00:37:00,110 --> 00:37:00,800
True, true.

967
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:01,190
Right?

968
00:37:01,190 --> 00:37:03,480
How can you charge
100 yuan a bottle?

969
00:37:04,260 --> 00:37:04,740
Wait.

970
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:07,110
How much a bottle?

971
00:37:07,110 --> 00:37:07,640
A hundred.

972
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:08,630
A hundred a bottle?

973
00:37:08,630 --> 00:37:09,110
Yeah.

974
00:37:09,130 --> 00:37:10,470
And I'm not just talking about one bottle.

975
00:37:10,470 --> 00:37:12,670
One bottle can be diluted into several.

976
00:37:14,540 --> 00:37:15,830
Then the profit...

977
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:17,360
is really something.

978
00:37:18,190 --> 00:37:19,000
Think about it.

979
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,790
If we just sell these few bottles,

980
00:37:21,820 --> 00:37:24,350
it equals a whole night's
profit from drinks.

981
00:37:24,620 --> 00:37:26,150
I think this is pretty good.

982
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:28,070
-It’s good.
-Da.

983
00:37:28,590 --> 00:37:29,360
I supply,

984
00:37:30,590 --> 00:37:31,320
you sell.

985
00:37:31,710 --> 00:37:34,000
We split it fifty-fifty.

986
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:39,630
Thanks.

987
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:42,670
What do you mean by that?

988
00:37:42,690 --> 00:37:43,780
Thanks.

989
00:37:44,050 --> 00:37:44,780
But no need.

990
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:47,360
You just think your cut is too small,

991
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:47,960
don't you?

992
00:37:48,550 --> 00:37:49,920
You definitely think that.

993
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:51,440
I didn't make myself clear.

994
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,590
With Blazing Phoenix and Great World,

995
00:37:52,590 --> 00:37:53,800
I split it seventy-thirty.

996
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:55,550
I took seventy. Really.

997
00:37:56,090 --> 00:37:57,490
It's not about the money.

998
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,480
How is it not about the money?

999
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:01,230
You didn't open this place to make money?

1000
00:38:01,230 --> 00:38:02,150
Then why?

1001
00:38:02,630 --> 00:38:03,440
To run a union?

1002
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:06,590
You really want to light up

1003
00:38:06,590 --> 00:38:07,590
the staff club again?

1004
00:38:07,590 --> 00:38:09,580
You think you're
standing up for something?

1005
00:38:09,580 --> 00:38:10,920
You actually hit the nail on the head.

1006
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:13,650
I just want to keep
the lights on in our dance hall.

1007
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:17,760
Da.

1008
00:38:18,510 --> 00:38:20,400
Do you know why everyone

1009
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:23,030
comes to our pitch-black
East Chemical Plant

1010
00:38:23,300 --> 00:38:24,700
to visit this dance hall?

1011
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:27,530
Is it because your place is fun?

1012
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:28,630
No.

1013
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:30,850
It's because this place...

1014
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:31,510
it...

1015
00:38:31,630 --> 00:38:33,670
doesn't belong to the system, right?

1016
00:38:33,670 --> 00:38:35,430
It's under
the Plant Security Department, isn't it?

1017
00:38:35,430 --> 00:38:36,320
With the factory in this state,

1018
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:37,720
no one has the energy to care.

1019
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:39,150
That's why it can exist here.

1020
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:40,840
If you try to run
a squeaky-clean dance hall,

1021
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,000
give it 6 months,

1022
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:45,660
and all the money you made
down south will go down the drain.

1023
00:38:51,070 --> 00:38:51,670
Boss Si.

1024
00:38:52,070 --> 00:38:52,590
Boss Si.

1025
00:38:53,150 --> 00:38:54,080
Please calm down.

1026
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:55,480
That is just how Tieda is.

1027
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:57,540
-It’s OK.
-He can pretend sometimes.

1028
00:38:58,300 --> 00:38:59,560
Don't take it to heart.

1029
00:39:03,190 --> 00:39:04,120
Is this your car?

1030
00:39:04,580 --> 00:39:06,240
Drove it back from Guangzhou.

1031
00:39:06,490 --> 00:39:07,340
Talk to Da.

1032
00:39:07,720 --> 00:39:09,720
If we partner up and make some money,

1033
00:39:10,230 --> 00:39:12,090
you can buy a car like this easily.

1034
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:12,920
Right.

1035
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:14,480
Boss Si.

1036
00:39:17,070 --> 00:39:18,330
Actually, Tieda and I,

1037
00:39:19,030 --> 00:39:20,880
we are just business partners.

1038
00:39:22,150 --> 00:39:23,350
If you need anything,

1039
00:39:23,350 --> 00:39:24,880
you can come to me directly.

1040
00:39:25,070 --> 00:39:25,960
We can talk.

1041
00:39:26,190 --> 00:39:27,050
Think about it.

1042
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:28,710
Does that work?

1043
00:39:28,710 --> 00:39:29,480
It works.

1044
00:39:30,460 --> 00:39:32,660
Zhigang, let me tell you one more thing.

1045
00:39:33,190 --> 00:39:34,190
Remember this.

1046
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:36,090
No matter what business you do,

1047
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,920
if others have what we don't,

1048
00:39:38,030 --> 00:39:39,490
forget about buying a car.

1049
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:40,640
See that?

1050
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:42,550
You'll be riding a tricycle every day.

1051
00:39:42,550 --> 00:39:42,880
Yes.

1052
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:43,360
I'm off.

1053
00:39:43,360 --> 00:39:44,490
Drive safe, Boss Si.

1054
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:45,560
Take care.

1055
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:48,230
Is this okay?

1056
00:39:48,230 --> 00:39:49,480
Sure. It suits you.

1057
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:08,490
Well, Da. Don't you understand

1058
00:40:09,190 --> 00:40:10,590
about the situation now?

1059
00:40:10,780 --> 00:40:12,090
I'm really curious

1060
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:14,160
why you're so stubborn.

1061
00:40:14,230 --> 00:40:15,110
You just said

1062
00:40:15,110 --> 00:40:17,360
you want to keep
the lights in our dance hall

1063
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:18,590
on, right?

1064
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:21,230
If we work with Wei Si,

1065
00:40:21,510 --> 00:40:23,070
you can swap every bulb for 200 watts.

1066
00:40:23,070 --> 00:40:24,670
There'd be no problem at all.

1067
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,400
I want the lights in our dance hall

1068
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:28,070
to shine clean.

1069
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:30,960
I don't know
if there's a problem with his goods

1070
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,220
or if they're illegal.

1071
00:40:32,220 --> 00:40:34,740
I just know his money
definitely isn't clean.

1072
00:40:34,740 --> 00:40:36,200
What's not clean about it?

1073
00:40:36,290 --> 00:40:37,640
We run a dance hall.

1074
00:40:37,710 --> 00:40:39,710
Can you guarantee every penny is clean?

1075
00:40:39,710 --> 00:40:40,800
That's different, okay?

1076
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:43,070
If they hook up
with customers behind our backs,

1077
00:40:43,070 --> 00:40:43,930
would you know?

1078
00:40:44,480 --> 00:40:45,540
That's different.

1079
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:47,510
Maybe they're actually dating.

1080
00:40:47,510 --> 00:40:48,070
Right?

1081
00:40:48,070 --> 00:40:49,000
I can't control that.

1082
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:52,000
All I know is my dance hall must be clean.

1083
00:40:52,180 --> 00:40:54,410
The venue attracts a certain kind of girl.

1084
00:40:54,410 --> 00:40:56,710
And the girls attract
a certain kind of guest.

1085
00:40:56,710 --> 00:40:57,880
What's the rush?

1086
00:40:57,880 --> 00:40:59,150
We've only been open for a few days.

1087
00:40:59,150 --> 00:40:59,960
Give it a rest.

1088
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:03,630
Bro, I'm sorry about that.

1089
00:41:03,630 --> 00:41:04,150
She...

1090
00:41:04,790 --> 00:41:07,270
She's just a little reckless.

1091
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:09,010
Xiaoman, come here.

1092
00:41:09,630 --> 00:41:10,490
Say something.

1093
00:41:11,320 --> 00:41:12,450
Try to persuade him.

1094
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:14,410
Well, about this...

1095
00:41:15,180 --> 00:41:16,960
I really shouldn't get involved in this.

1096
00:41:16,960 --> 00:41:19,280
But there was a coworker
in my factory before,

1097
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:20,590
my senior.

1098
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:21,820
He drank that stuff

1099
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:23,490
every day. He got addicted.

1100
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:25,820
Then he drank too much
and was dazed all day long.

1101
00:41:25,820 --> 00:41:27,250
Last time, because he was drinking that,

1102
00:41:27,250 --> 00:41:29,380
he blew up our workshop while welding.

1103
00:41:30,150 --> 00:41:31,800
We all had to take responsibility.

1104
00:41:31,800 --> 00:41:34,190
So I agree with Da's idea.

1105
00:41:34,230 --> 00:41:35,360
Even if we earn a bit less,

1106
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:35,960
don't cause trouble.

1107
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:37,840
It's easy

1108
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:38,960
for you to say.

1109
00:41:41,150 --> 00:41:43,230
You still have
that clothing business, right?

1110
00:41:43,230 --> 00:41:44,630
If I remember correctly.

1111
00:41:45,110 --> 00:41:45,760
Over here,

1112
00:41:45,760 --> 00:41:47,280
you stay if you're having fun.

1113
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:48,760
If not, you leave.

1114
00:41:48,910 --> 00:41:49,910
We're different.

1115
00:41:51,410 --> 00:41:52,960
This is where we make a living.

1116
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:54,630
We depend on this dance hall to survive.

1117
00:41:54,630 --> 00:41:55,690
Do you understand?

1118
00:41:57,110 --> 00:41:58,210
Zhigang, you...

1119
00:41:59,990 --> 00:42:01,630
I talked to Da before.

1120
00:42:02,220 --> 00:42:03,680
I have two things going on,

1121
00:42:03,830 --> 00:42:04,240
right?

1122
00:42:04,270 --> 00:42:05,590
Running back and forth.

1123
00:42:05,590 --> 00:42:06,710
But I never said

1124
00:42:06,710 --> 00:42:08,150
I'd stay there all day
and never come here.

1125
00:42:08,150 --> 00:42:09,320
I spend most of my time

1126
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:10,880
at our dance hall.

1127
00:42:11,510 --> 00:42:13,150
It's not like I'm fully committed there

1128
00:42:13,150 --> 00:42:14,750
and neglecting things here.

1129
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:16,480
I don't mean anything else.

1130
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:18,880
I'm just saying
let's not look for trouble.

1131
00:42:19,890 --> 00:42:20,520
Fine.

1132
00:42:22,150 --> 00:42:23,680
You're all high and mighty.

1133
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:25,190
I'm the only snob, right?

1134
00:42:25,190 --> 00:42:26,880
Wait, what are you doing?

1135
00:42:30,190 --> 00:42:31,050
Wait, Zhigang.

1136
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:33,080
Don't be in such a rush, okay?

1137
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:34,880
Hasn't the reputation of our dance hall

1138
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,110
already spread?

1139
00:42:36,300 --> 00:42:38,450
You said we'd make
2,000 a day, right?

1140
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:40,280
We'll definitely make money in the future.

1141
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:41,480
Don't you understand the situation?

1142
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:42,320
When I said that,

1143
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,190
